Four travellers on Thursday evening, lost their lives in a car accident along Kaduna-Abuja road. The accident, which left four others in serious injuries, involved a trailer and Peugeot 406. A resident of Kateri village where the accident occurred, Alhaji Musa Wada told DAILYPOST on Thursday evening at Kateri community that the accident was caused because of over-speeding. “Wallahi, the speed on this road is terrible. But the road was extremely bad. Potholes everywhere, yet commercial vehicles and road users are always in a hurry. “The Peugeot 406 was heading towards Kaduna and jerked off the road, rammed into a trailer. Four died instantly, while four others sustained serious injuries,” he said The sector Commander, Federal Road Safety Corps, Kaduna State Command did not pick his calls.